 {"id":"bd-qhgx","title":"time: execute time_ops.json fixture family through harness matrix","description":"Concrete gap: crates/frankenlibc-harness/tests/time_ops_conformance_test.rs currently validates fixture metadata and coverage counts only. Add isolated harness subprocess execution for tests/conformance/fixtures/time_ops.json, assert expected_output and host parity by mode, and fix any matrix-path regressions the new coverage exposes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T04:52:11.487227287Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T12:52:57.157025105Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T12:52:57.154561752Z","close_reason":"Added time_ops_fixture_cases_match_execute_fixture_case (in-process) and time_ops_fixture_executes_with_host_parity_via_harness_matrix (subprocess) — covers time/clock/clock_gettime/localtime_r fixture cases via both paths. Gates clean via rch + isolated CARGO_TARGET_DIR.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"bd-qij6l","title":"printf %n disabled by FORTIFY but fixture expects it to work","description":"Modern glibc disables %n in snprintf for security (FORTIFY_SOURCE). Our impl honors it. Fixture sprintf_n_count_mid in printf_conformance.json expects the cross-impl comparison to succeed, but host glibc refuses %n so host_output is empty while our impl emits 'hello'. Either the fixture should be removed/hardened-only, or the comparison should tolerate the host's security-hardening difference.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T05:34:31.156927535Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:34:31.156927535Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
